## Overview

This document outlines the best practices, conventions, and standards for the ABUVI frontend application. The frontend uses **Vue 3** with the **Composition API**, **PrimeVue** components, and **Tailwind CSS** for styling, built with **Vite** and **TypeScript**.

For core principles (TDD, incremental changes, type safety) and language standards (English only), refer to [base-standards.mdc](./base-standards.mdc).

## Technology Stack

### Core Technologies

- **Vue 3**: Modern framework with Composition API
- **TypeScript**: Type-safe development with strict mode
- **Vite**: Fast build tool and development server
- **Vue Router**: Client-side routing and navigation

### UI Framework

- **PrimeVue**: Rich component library (tables, dialogs, calendars, forms)
- **Tailwind CSS**: Utility-first CSS framework for styling
- **Leaflet.js**: Lightweight interactive maps (historical camp locations)
- **Driver.js** (`^1.3.x`): Lightweight (~5 KB gzipped) in-app onboarding/tour library with zero dependencies

### State Management and Data Flow

- **Pinia**: Official Vue 3 state management (global/shared state)
- **Composition API**: `ref`, `reactive`, `computed` for local component state
- **Composables**: Reusable logic encapsulated in `useXxx` functions
- **Axios**: HTTP client for API communication

### Testing Framework

- **Vitest**: Unit and component testing (Vite-native, fast)
- **Vue Test Utils**: Vue component testing utilities
- **Cypress**: End-to-end testing for user workflows
- **Coverage Threshold**: 90% for branches, functions, lines, and statements

### Development Tools

- **ESLint**: Code linting with Vue-specific rules
- **Prettier**: Code formatting
- **TypeScript**: Static type checking
- **Vite Dev Server**: Hot module replacement (HMR)

